The paper discusses a method for sampling large unknown Internet topologies, which falls under the category of network analysis. The paper also discusses the bias in the Breadth First Search (BFS) approach and proposes a correction procedure, which falls under the category of data analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.SD (Software Engineering), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
